<section>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="row text-center my-sm-2 mt-5">
        <div class="faq-section mb-3 col-lg-10 mx-auto">
  
        <div class="faq-header bg-gradient-primary">
            Some Frequently Asked Questions
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question bg-gradient-primary">
                Will you be listing my house on the MLS or actually buying it?
                <i class="fas fa-plus"></i>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer"style="display: block;" >
                <p>As professional home buyers, we don’t act as real estate agents and we don’t list houses. Instead, we purchase houses in the Central Florida area that meet our specific purchasing criteria.</p>
                <p>Once we buy your house, we may choose to repair it and resell it to another homeowner, keep it as a rental property, or sell it to a financial partner.</p>
                <p>Regardless of what we do with the property, you’ll receive the agreed-upon price for your house.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question bg-gradient-primary">
                Do you pay fair prices for properties?
                <i class="fas fa-plus"></i>
            </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer" >
                <p> We typically purchase houses at a discount to the top market value, as we need to resell them at a profit to another homeowner.<br>
However, we always strive to provide a fair and reasonable price for the property we are purchasing.<br>

We understand that many sellers need to sell their home quickly, and we are able to offer a quick and hassle-free cash sale, without requiring the seller to make any repairs or pay any agent fees.<br>

If you are looking for a fast and easy sale, we are happy to work with you to find a price that works for both parties.<br>
And of course, our no-obligation pricing commitment means that you are under no obligation to move forward with the offer we provide. </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question bg-gradient-primary">
                How do you determine the price to offer on my house?
                <i class="fas fa-plus"></i>
            </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer" >
                <p>Our approach is transparent and straightforward. We evaluate the location of the property, <br>its current condition, any repairs that may be needed, and recent sales of comparable properties in the area.
<br>Based on these factors, we are able to offer a fair price that works for both parties.
<br>
We always take the time to explain our reasoning and calculations to our clients, so they can be confident that they are receiving a fair offer.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <a href="/faq" class="btn bg-gradient-primary read-more">READ MORE</a>
    </div>
    
      </div>
    </div>
</div>
</section>

    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.15.3/js/all.min.js"></script>
 <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-question').forEach(item => {
    item.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const answer = item.nextElementSibling;
        const allAnswers = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-answer');
        allAnswers.forEach(ans => ans.style.display = 'none');
        if (answer.style.display === 'block') {
            answer.style.display = 'none';
        } else {
            answer.style.display = 'block';
        }
    });
});
document.querySelectorAll('.faq-answer').forEach(item => {
    item.style.transition = 'max-height 0.5s ease-in-out';
});
document.querySelectorAll('.faq-question').forEach(item => {
    item.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const answer = item.nextElementSibling;
        if (answer.style.maxHeight) {
            answer.style.maxHeight = null;
        } else {
            answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px';
        }
    });
});
</script>